# Hallucination Detection Middleware v3 — Cline Context

## Project Stack
- **Backend**: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, ChromaDB (vector DB), BM25 hybrid search
- **Frontend**: React 18, Vite, Recharts, TailwindCSS
- **Active LLM**: NVIDIA NIM cloud GPU inference (OpenAI-compatible API)
  - Extractor: meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct
  - Verifier: meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct
- **Local LLM fallback**: Ollama with phi3:mini or mistral:7b

## Architecture
```
Request → ClaimExtractor → Verifier (KB + Web-RAG) → DecisionEngine → SelfCorrector → Response
                                  ↓
                         ClaimCache (semantic + Redis + in-memory)
```

## Key Conventions
- All LLM clients use `AsyncOpenAI` — NIM is OpenAI-compatible, no special client needed
- Category field: `MEDICAL | LEGAL | FINANCIAL | GENERAL` — flows through ExtractedClaim → ClaimDecision → proxy → frontend
- Domain block thresholds: MEDICAL=0.95, LEGAL=0.90, FINANCIAL=0.85, GENERAL=0.40
- Cache class is `ClaimCache` (not VerificationCache) in `cache.py`
- Corrector class is `SelfCorrector` (not Corrector) in `corrector.py`
- Never write directly to `audit_trail.jsonl` — use `AuditTrail` class methods

## Entry Points
```bash
python run_proxy.py        # Start server → http://localhost:8080
python demo.py             # Run 4 test cases through pipeline
python evaluate.py --cases eval_cases.yaml  # Evaluate 26 test cases
python benchmark.py        # Measure latency/throughput
python ingest_wikipedia.py "Topic"  # Add Wikipedia article to KB
```

## Feature Flags (.env)
```ini
LLM_PROVIDER=nvidia_nim        # Active provider
WEB_RAG_ENABLED=true           # Falls back to web search when KB score < 0.40
SELF_CORRECTION_ENABLED=true   # Rewrites flagged/blocked claims
MPC_ENABLED=false              # Off by default — expensive (3N LLM calls)
BM25_ENABLED=true              # Hybrid BM25 + vector search
SEMANTIC_CACHE_ENABLED=true    # Cosine-similarity cache for verified claims
RERANKER_ENABLED=false         # Cross-encoder re-ranking (GPU-accelerated)
```

## Important File Paths
- `hallucination_middleware/config.py` — all settings (Pydantic BaseSettings)
- `hallucination_middleware/models.py` — ExtractedClaim, ClaimDecision, HallucinationAudit
- `hallucination_middleware/pipeline.py` — orchestrates full pipeline
- `hallucination_middleware/proxy.py` — FastAPI app, all HTTP endpoints
- `hallucination_middleware/audit_trail.py` — JSONL audit log + stats
- `frontend/src/api.js` — all frontend API calls
- `frontend/src/components/Dashboard.jsx` — live monitoring charts
- `frontend/src/components/Playground.jsx` — interactive claim testing UI

## GPU Support
- sentence-transformers and ChromaDB embeddings auto-use CUDA when `torch` + NVIDIA GPU present
- Check: `python -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available())"`
- NVIDIA NIM handles LLM GPU inference in the cloud (no local GPU needed for LLM)
